The paper proposes a deep learning approach for abnormality detection in chest X-rays using image inpainting. This involves training a context encoder model on healthy X-rays to reconstruct missing patches. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves medical imaging and diagnosis, which suggests it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), medical imaging (cs.MED), and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
